choices.text: Sam has a list with a single element n. Then he has to perform certain operations on this list. In each operation Sam must remove any element x, such that x > 1, from the list and insert at the same position $\lfloor \frac{x}{2} \rfloor$, $x \operatorname{mod} 2$, $\lfloor \frac{x}{2} \rfloor$ sequentially. He must continue with these operations until all the elements in the list are either 0 or 1. Now the masters want the total number of 1s in the range l to r (1-indexed).
